                             Content for this page

                                  NINDS Plans

   Get Web page suited for printing
   Email this to a friend or colleague
     __________________________________________________________________

   NINDS has a number of planning documents that define its priorities in
   one or more areas related to its mission.

     NINDS Vision

     NINDS Strategic Plan, or "Neuroscience in the New Millenium," is the
   first strategic research plan for the National Institute of
   Neurological Disorders and Stroke and defines priorities for the
   institute's research funding.

     Strategic Plan Implementation Supplement describes the actions NINDS
   is taking to implement the strategic research plan.

     Five-Year Plan on Minority Health Disparities. This plan describes
   areas of research emphasis to reduce and/or eliminate minority health
   disparities.

     Parkinson's Disease Research Agenda. This document describes NINDS'
   plans and priorities for Parkinson's disease research. For more
   information, please visit the Parkinson's Disease Research Web Site.

     Report of the Brain Tumor Progress Review Group results from a joint
   effort by NINDS and NCI to organize and prioritize a national agenda
   for brain tumor research. More about the Brain Tumor Progress Review
   Group.

     "Benchmarks" For Epilepsy Research result from the "Curing Epilepsy:
   Focus on the Future" conference held in March 2000 and are a first step
   toward the future NINDS Research Agenda for Epilepsy.

   Reviewed July 1, 2001
